
---


@startuml

' Define classes with attributes and methods
class Doctor {
    +numericPractitionerNumber: String
    +signature: Image
    +fullName: String
    +address: String
    +phoneNumber: String
    +requisitions: List<Requisition>
}

class Patient {
    +healthNumber: String
    +firstName: String
    +lastName: String
    +dateOfBirth: Date
    +address: String
    +phoneNumber: String
    +appointments: List<Appointment>
    +requisitions: List<Requisition>
}

class Requisition {
    +validFrom: Date
    +tests: List<Test>
    +repetitionPattern: RepetitionPattern
    +repetitionCount: Integer
    +interval: Interval
    +doctor: Doctor
    +patient: Patient
}

class Test {
    +testName: String
    +duration: Duration
    +isWalkInOnly: Boolean
    +requiresAppointment: Boolean
    +belongsToGroup: String
    +requisitions: List<Requisition>
}

class Appointment {
    +confirmationNumber: String
    +date: Date
    +startTime: Time
    +endTime: Time
    +lab: Lab
    +requisition: Requisition
    +patient: Patient
}

class Lab {
    +registrationNumber: String
    +name: String
    +address: String
    +businessHours: BusinessHours
    +appointments: List<Appointment>
    +tests: List<Test>
}

class RepetitionPattern {
    +patternType: String
}

class Interval {
    +intervalType: String
}

class Duration {
    +durationValue: Integer
    +unit: String
}

class BusinessHours {
    +openEveryDay: Boolean
    +dailyStartTime: Time
    +dailyEndTime: Time
}

class Result {
    +test: Test
    +report: String
    +status: String
    +doctor: Doctor
    +patient: Patient
}

' Relationships
Doctor --> Requisition
Patient --> Requisition
Patient --> Appointment
Doctor --> Appointment
Requisition --> Test
Test --> Requisition
Requisition --> RepetitionPattern
Requisition --> Interval
Appointment --> Lab
Appointment --> Requisition
Appointment --> Patient
Lab --> Appointment
Lab --> Test
Test --> Duration
Test --> BusinessHours
Doctor --> Doctor "0..1" "can prescribe to self"
Doctor --> Doctor "0..*" "can prescribe to others"

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:
- **Association**: Arrows show one-way associations between classes.
- **Multiplicity**: Some multiplicity notations are implied (e.g., `Doctor --> Doctor "0..1"` means a doctor can prescribe to themselves or others).
- **Aggregation/Composition**: Not explicitly shown but can be inferred from relationships (e.g., `Requisition` has a list of `Test`s).
- **Attributes**:
  - Primitive types like `String`, `Date`, `Time`, `Integer`, etc., are used where appropriate.
  - Complex types like `Duration`, `BusinessHours`, and `RepetitionPattern` are represented as separate classes if needed for modeling.

